                "invention-title": [
                    "Method for measuring hydrogen and helium content in gas",
                    "用于测量气体中氢氦含量的方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The embodiment of the invention relates to the technical field of testing or analyzing materials by means of measuring chemical or physical properties of the materials, in particular to a method for measuring the content of hydrogen and helium in gas, the method utilizes a mass spectrum measuring piece to measure the content of hydrogen and helium in the gas, and the method comprises the following steps: adjusting measuring parameters of the mass spectrum measuring piece, when a mass spectrum measuring piece is used for measuring gas, tritium gas in the gas is prevented from being ionized into tritium ions. And measuring the hydrogen content and the helium content in the gas by using a mass spectrum measuring piece. According to the measuring method provided by the embodiment of the invention, the tritium gas in the gas is prevented from being ionized into the tritium ions, so that the accuracy of measuring the hydrogen and helium content in the gas can be improved."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本申请的实施例涉及借助于测定材料的化学或物理性质来测试或分析材料技术领域，特别涉及一种用于测量气体中氢氦含量的方法，该方法利用质谱测量件测量气体中的氢含量和氦含量，该方法包括：调节质谱测量件的测量参数，以在利用质谱测量件对气体进行测量时，避免将气体中的氚气电离为氚离子；利用质谱测量件测量气体中的氢含量和氦含量。本申请的实施例提供的测量方法，通过避免将气体中的氚气电离为氚离子，能够提高测量气体中氢氦含量的准确性。"
                }
            ]
